{"id":"6447","name":"bright-early-the-sun-also-rises-edition","title":"Bright &amp; Early: The Sun Also Rises Edition","author":"Christy Frink","date":"2011-01-28T10:30:00-06:00","tags":["ayp","budget cuts","child prostitution","jeff fisher","job growth","marching band","metro council","metro finance department","mnps","nclb","prom dresses","recession","road salt","sex trafficking","titans","tsu"],"categories":["News"],"contentEncoded":"<div id=\"greet_block\"><noscript><div class=\"greet_block wpgb_cornered\"><div class=\"greet_text\"><div class=\"greet_image\"><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/feed/rss/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://nashvillest.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-greet-box/images/rss_icon.png\" alt=\"WP Greet Box icon\"></a></div>Hello there! If you&apos;re new to Nashvillest, you might want to <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/nashvillest\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>subscribe to our RSS feed</strong></a> to make sure you don&apos;t miss anything! We&apos;re also on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/#!/nashvillest\" target=\"blank\"><strong>Twitter</strong></a> if you&apos;d like to join us there!<div style=\"clear:both\"></div><div class=\"greet_block_powered_by\">Powered by <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/projects/wordpress-plugins/wp-greet-box-wordpress-plugin/\" title=\"WP Greet Box WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WP Greet Box</a> <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/\" title=\"WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WordPress Plugin</a></div><div style=\"clear:both\"></div></div></div></noscript></div><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/24703734@N02/5390134669/in/pool-715021@N24/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.flickr.com&apos;]);\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://farm6.static.flickr.com/5094/5390134669_b823d3ba41.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"375\"></a></p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">Good morning, Nashville. By the looks of the headlines this morning, you would think that nothing else is going on in the world besides <a href=\"http://www.wkrn.com/Global/story.asp?S=13923087\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wkrn.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">the Titans kicking Jeff Fisher to the curb</a>. Nevertheless, <a href=\"http://wpln.org/?p=23559\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;wpln.org&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">the federal government has ruled that Metro Schools must allow students in underperforming schools to transfer to better ones</a>. Though this is standard procedures when schools don&#x2019;t meet their Adequate Yearly Progress (AYP) goals under No Child Left Behind, Metro had hoped to appeal the procedure because standardized testing scores were so late coming in this year. As a result, they&#x2019;ll be sending out one letter to parents letting them know that students can transfer and another trying to persuade them not to.</p><ul><li><strong>Budget cuts for Metro. </strong>Metro&#x2019;s finance director <a href=\"http://nashvillecitypaper.com/content/city-news/metro-departments-asked-analyze-3-percent-budget-cuts?utm_source=feedburner&amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;utm_campaign=Feed:+NashvilleCityPaper-LatestNews+(Nashville+City+Paper+-+Latest+News)&amp;utm_content=Google+Reader\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;nashvillecitypaper.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">sent out a memo this week asking all departments to figure out how they would be affected by a 3% budget cut</a>, indicating that something like that might be in the cards.</li><li><strong>Job growth in 2011. </strong>Economists predict that <a href=\"http://wpln.org/?p=23536\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;wpln.org&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">jobs will grow pretty steadily this year, but there probably won&#x2019;t be any sort of magic boom in employment numbers</a>. In all likelihood, they say, it may be 2014 before things return to pre-recession normal.</li><li><strong>Bits &amp; pieces. </strong>If you have any old prom dresses lying around, <a href=\"http://www.wkrn.com/Global/story.asp?S=13922944\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wkrn.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">consider giving them to these folks</a> &#x2026; <a href=\"http://www.wsmv.com/news/26643105/detail.html\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wsmv.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Yes, we get it, everyone is out of road salt</a> &#x2026; <a href=\"http://wpln.org/?p=23534\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;wpln.org&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">TSU apparently has a pretty killer marching band</a> &#x2026; Several legislators are <a href=\"http://nashvillecitypaper.com/content/city-news/state-bill-aims-curtail-child-prostitution-human-trafficking?utm_source=feedburner&amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;utm_campaign=Feed:+NashvilleCityPaper-CityNews+(Nashville+City+Paper+-+City+News)&amp;utm_content=Google+Reader\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;nashvillecitypaper.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">teaming up to combat child prostitution and sex trafficking in Tennessee</a> &#x2026; Please enjoy this <a href=\"http://nashvillewx.com/2011/01/nicer-weather-over-the-next-couple-of-days/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;nashvillewx.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_self\">lovely snow-free forecast for the next couple of days</a>.</li></ul><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em>Photo by <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/24703734@N02/5390134669/in/pool-715021@N24/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.flickr.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Alyssa Reeves</a>.</em></p><p>Related posts:<ol><li><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/2011/01/25/bright-early-blah-blah-blah-snow-edition/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: Bright &amp; Early: Blah Blah Blah Snow Edition\">Bright &amp; Early: Blah Blah Blah Snow Edition</a></li><li><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/2010/12/16/bright-early-a-drop-in-the-bucket-edition-2/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: Bright &amp; Early: A Drop In The Bucket Edition\">Bright &amp; Early: A Drop In The Bucket Edition</a></li></ol></p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<!--END .entry-content .article-->"}